xbrlcore.linkbase
Class PresentationLinkbase

java.lang.Object
  xbrlcore.linkbase.Linkbase
      xbrlcore.linkbase.PresentationLinkbase
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class PresentationLinkbase
extends Linkbase

This class represents a presentation linkbase of a DTS. The purpose of this linkbase is to structure the elements in a hierarchical order.

Author:
Daniel Hamm

Method Detail

buildPresentationLinkbase

public void buildPresentationLinkbase()
This method builds the presentation linkbase. More detailed, the hierarchical structure of the elements is built. This structure is built in various PresentationLinkbaseElement objects.

getPresentationLinkbaseElementListForTaxonomy

public java.util.List getPresentationLinkbaseElementListForTaxonomy(java.lang.String taxonomyName,
                                                                    java.lang.String extendedLinkRole)
                                                             throws XBRLCoreException
Returns a list of PresentationLinkbaseElement objects according to the presentation linkbase. The list already is in correct order.

Parameters:
taxonomyName - The name of the taxonomy of which the presentation shall be obtained (if NULL, the whole DTS is taken).
extendedLinkRole - Extended link role from which the presentation shall be obtained (if NULL, the default link role is taken).
Returns:
List of xbrlcore.linkbase.PresentationLinkbaseElement objects.
Throws:
XBRLCoreException

getPresentationLinkbaseElementListForConcept

public java.util.List getPresentationLinkbaseElementListForConcept(Concept concept,
                                                                   java.lang.String extendedLinkRole)
Returns a list of PresentationLinkbaseElement objects which form the hierarchical presentation tree below a given concept.

Parameters:
concept - Root of the hierarchical presentation tree which is returned.
extendedLinkRole - Extended link role of the presentation linkbase.
Returns:
Hierarchical presentation tree with concept being the root.

getPresentationLinkbaseElementList

public java.util.List getPresentationLinkbaseElementList(java.lang.String taxonomyName)
                                                  throws XBRLCoreException
Returns a list of PresentationLinkbaseElement objects according to the default link role (http://www.xbrl.org/2003/role/link) of the presentation linkbase which belong to a certain taxonomy within the DTS. The list already is in correct order.

Parameters:
taxonomyName - Name of the taxonomy within the DTS the elements have to belong to.
Returns:
List of xbrlcore.linkbase.PresentationLinkbaseElement objects.
Throws:
XBRLCoreException

getPresentationLinkbaseElementRoot

public java.util.List getPresentationLinkbaseElementRoot(java.lang.String extendedLinkRole)
Returns root elements of the presentation linkbase.

Parameters:
extendedLinkRole - Extended link role of the presentation linkbase.
Returns:
List A list with all the elements which are root elements in the presentation linkbase (that means, which have no parent element) in a specific extended link role.
